      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LAVERS GINNY (6) stuck on well last time to finish 0.8 lengths back in second (16.83) at this track in a Grade 5 over 300m. Didn't win last time but still ran one of the quickest times on the card. Well-placed to take this out. MCCREERY (8) comes off an average effort last start when eighth at this track over 350m behind Mystery Nell (20.38) in a T3 RSTW. Should be in this for a long way. MR. BILLY LEE (2) was far too good after leading them home to make it back to back wins, scoring at Geelong over 400m (22.79). Can continue on with his winning form. RED RIVER ROGUE (7) picked up a cheque last time and is in the mix again.",
